---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout
  title="Calories vs Kilocalories: What You Actually Burn"
  description="The confusing cal/kcal distinction explained. Understand what food labels mean and how energy units work."
  keywords="calories vs kilocalories, kcal vs cal, food calories, energy units, calorie confusion, kilojoules, food energy"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Energy</span>
      </nav>

      <BlogCrossLinks title="Calories vs Kilocalories: What You Actually Burn" />

      <!-- Article Meta -->
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2025-06-14">June 14, 2025</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Lead Paragraph -->
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
        When someone says "this has 200 calories," they actually mean 200 kilocalories. The terminology is confusing because everyday language and scientific language use "calorie" to mean different things. Here is the full explanation.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: The Distinction -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">The Distinction</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-6 my-6 not-prose shadow-sm">
        <div class="space-y-2 text-center">
          <p class="text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">1 food Calorie (Cal) = 1 kilocalorie (kcal) = 1,000 calories (cal)</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">The capital-C Calorie on food labels = 1 kcal</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Small calorie (cal):</strong> Energy to heat 1 gram of water by 1°C — used in chemistry</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Large Calorie (Cal/kcal):</strong> Energy to heat 1 kilogram of water by 1°C — used on food labels</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Kilojoule (kJ):</strong> The SI unit. 1 kcal = 4.184 kJ</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section: Food Labels -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Reading Food Labels</h2>
      <p>Different countries display energy differently:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>US/Canada:</strong> "Calories" (meaning kcal)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Europe:</strong> Shows both kJ and kcal</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Australia/NZ:</strong> Primarily kJ, sometimes kcal in brackets</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>To convert: kJ ÷ 4.2 ≈ kcal (food Calories)</p>

      <!-- Section: Daily Numbers -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Daily Energy Needs</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Average adult:</strong> 2,000-2,500 kcal/day (8,400-10,500 kJ/day)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Sedentary:</strong> Closer to 1,800 kcal</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Very active:</strong> Up to 3,500+ kcal</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Marathon runner (race day):</strong> Burns ~2,600 kcal during the race alone</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section: Why It Matters -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Why This Matters</h2>
      <p>The confusion is mostly academic — everyone in everyday life uses "calorie" to mean kcal. But it matters when:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Reading scientific papers (they use small calories)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Converting between kJ and kcal for international food labels</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Programming nutrition apps (use kcal internally to avoid 1000x errors)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Converter CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 dark:from-amber-900/20 dark:to-orange-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">
            🔗 Try our free energy converter
          </p>
          <a
            href="/convert/energy"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Open Converter →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Back to Blog -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">
          ← Back to all articles
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
